Author:  FEATON
Vol / Page:  50
Edition:
Quote:  HYPERICUM GRAMINEUM (<i>Forst.</i>) ... The leaves of some of the British species were formerly applied to fresh wounds, which they were supposed to heal; hence the plant was called in French <i>Toutesaine</i> - corrupted into Tutsan, its common English name.
