Author:  HILGENDORF
Vol / Page:  125
Edition:  1967
Quote:  TUTSAN (<i>Hypericum</i> and <i>rosaemum</i>), is a similar [to St. John's wort] but the less common weed. It is widely spread usually near the bush edge in both islands.] ... Tutsan is a corruption of Fr. Toutsaine- meaning heal-all.
